data.meta_description: An online exhibition that examines the Stonewall rebellion of 1969 in the context of the social upheaval of the period, the burgeoning gay liberation movement and the creation of LGBT identities.  The project includes oral histories and explores storytelling and collective memory surrounding the Stonewall rebellion. Through the voices, documents, written accounts and images shared here, the visitor is introduced to the complexity, diversity and uniqueness of LGBT experiences.
